[My thought process in commenting on the state of the polio eradication effort is one of "good news" and "not so good news". In this current weekly update the good news includes no mention of newly confirmed cases of WPV1 associated disease in Pakistan and no mention of newly isolated WPV1 in environmental samples in Pakistan. It also includes the continued absence of newly confirmed cases of cVDPV2 in Syria and of cVDPV1 in Papua New Guinea. And a very cautious absence of newly confirmed cases of cVDPV in the Democratic Republic of the Congo and in Somalia.

The not so good news includes the advanced notification of confirmation of a WPV1 case in Kandar Afghanistan and the confirmation of a cVDPV2 associated case in Yobe State, Nigeria (Yobe state Nigeria is the western neighbor of Borno state see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Nigeria_states_map) as well as the advanced notifications of cVDPV2 positive environmental samples from Yobe and Sokoto states, indicating continued circulation of these cVDPV2 in northern Nigeria, and of WPV1 in Afghanistan.

A map showing the global locations of WPV1 and cVDPV cases of polio can be found at http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/.

