communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The report above highlights the challenges facing the goal of polio eradication in the face of persistent zones of civil unrest, where vaccinations are not readily available, nor is acute flaccid paralysis (AFP) surveillance up to par. Genetic data on the viruses isolated from sewage samples demonstrate that there have been cVDPVs being transmitted in the Horn of Africa, undetected for more than 3 years. This further reinforces my sense that declaration of a polio free status in an area after 3 years have passed without virus isolation may well be risky.

The good news is that the isolation of a virus in Nairobi that is related to viruses in Somalia, was only found in one sampling location, suggesting the virus may have recently been imported into Nairobi, although genetically the virus has been circulating undetected for more than 1 year.

A map of the Horn of Africa can be found at: https://tinyurl.com/y85x9bwz. An excellent map of the Horn of Africa showing locations of environmental surveillance sites can be found at the source URL. - Mod.MPP]

